        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Dimensions</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">30" x 38" x 43" (Bare Centrifuge)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Motor Power</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">7.5 HP</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Voltages</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">230 / 460 V; 3-Phase</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Material of Construction -->
  <h2 id="material">Material of Construction</h2>
  <p>
    The Alfa Laval MOPX 207 is designed for mineral oil and fuel separation applications. Therefore, the material used in its construction is well suited for such uses. The following table lists the various components of the centrifuge and the material it is made of.
  </p>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose">
    <table class="w-full text-sm text-text border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-navy text-white">
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold w-1/2">Component</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Material</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Bowl Body &amp; Bowl Hood</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Disc Stack</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Distributor or Disc Carrier</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Top Disc</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Top Covers (Collecting)</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Silium (Aluminum Alloy)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3">Frame</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Nodular Cast Iron</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Banner -->
  <div class="bg-navy text-white rounded-xl p-6 my-8 text-center not-prose">
    <p class="text-sm">
      If you have simple, routine questions: We have condensed our 40+ years of disc-stack centrifuge experience into
      <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-faq/" class="underline font-bold hover:text-gold">101 Frequently Asked Questions about Disc Stack Centrifuges!</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- WHPX 407 Section -->
  <h2 id="whpx-407">Alfa Laval WHPX 407 — Partial-Discharge Disc-Stack Centrifuge</h2>
  <p>
    The Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge is a self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge designed for the three-phase separation of fuel oils, such as <a href="/fuel-oil-centrifuge/">light fuel oil</a> (LFO).
  </p>
  <p>
    With a <strong>10 HP Motor</strong>, the WHPX 407 centrifuge has a bowl RPM of <strong>7,125</strong> and can process <strong>25 GPM of ISO 180 cSt Light Fuel Oil</strong>.
  </p>
  <p>
    Also, the WHPX-407 is a <strong>partial-discharge centrifuge</strong>. This means that this centrifuge is capable of discharging only the accumulated sludge and minimizing <a href="/centrifuge-product-loss-during-discharge/">fluid loss</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-center not-prose">
    <figure class="flex-shrink-0">
      <img
        src="/images/alfa-laval-mopx-207-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-WHPX510-DAF.webp"
        alt="Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge System with 60 kW Electric heater for light fuel oil separation"
        width="450"
        height="450"
        loading="lazy"
        class="rounded-lg"
      />
      <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge System with 60 kW Electric heater</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <div class="flex-1">
      <h3 id="applications-whpx" class="text-lg font-semibold text-navy mb-3">Alfa Laval WHPX-407 Applications</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text mb-3">
        Similar to the Alfa Laval MOPX-207, the WHPX-407 finds many applications in all kinds of 3-phase separation duties. Some of the popular applications are:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/fuel-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy hover:text-gold p-1.5 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-gold">&#x279C;</span> Light Fuel Oil</a></li>
        <li><a href="/machine-coolant-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy hover:text-gold p-1.5 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-gold">&#x279C;</span> Machining Coolant</a></li>
        <li><a href="/quench-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy hover:text-gold p-1.5 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-gold">&#x279C;</span> Quench Oil</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cutting-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy hover:text-gold p-1.5 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-gold">&#x279C;</span> Cutting Oil</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cutting-oil-centrifuge/#draw-oil" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-navy hover:text-gold p-1.5 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-gold">&#x279C;</span> Draw Oil</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- WHPX Specifications -->
  <h3 id="specifications-whpx">Alfa Laval WHPX-407 Specifications</h3>
  <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose">
    <table class="w-full text-sm text-text border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-navy text-white">
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold w-1/2">Parameter</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Model Type</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Alfa Laval WHPX 407 TGD 24-60</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Rated Capacity</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">25 GPM on 180 cSt Light Fuel Oil</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Sludge Space</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">1.30 Gallons</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
