  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions — Alfa Laval MOPX 207</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 not-prose">
    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5" open>
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer group-open:mb-3">What is the capacity of the Alfa Laval MOPX 207 centrifuge?</summary>
      <p class="text-text text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The Alfa Laval MOPX 207 can process 28 GPM of 13 cSt diesel fuel, 22 GPM of turbine lube oil, and 20 GPM of hydraulic oil. When processing distillate, the capacity increases to 32 GPM. It can also process over 30 Gallons per Minute of condensate, making it a highly versatile centrifuge for fuel and oil purification applications.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer group-open:mb-3">What is the difference between the MOPX 207, WHPX 407, and WSPX 207?</summary>
      <p class="text-text text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The MOPX 207 is a full-discharge purifier designed for fuel and mineral oil separation with a 7.5 HP motor and 6,325 RPM bowl speed. The WHPX 407 is a partial-discharge centrifuge with a larger 10 HP motor and 7,125 RPM bowl speed, designed for fuel oils like light fuel oil (LFO) at 25 GPM. The WSPX 207 is a concentrator designed for water-based liquids such as machine coolants and washer fluids, with a 7.5 HP motor and 6,400 RPM bowl speed processing 20 GPM. The partial-discharge models (WHPX and WSPX) minimize fluid loss during sludge ejection.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer group-open:mb-3">What materials is the MOPX 207 bowl made from?</summary>
      <p class="text-text text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The MOPX 207 bowl body and bowl hood are constructed from 316L Duplex Stainless Steel, as is the disc stack. The distributor (disc carrier) and top disc are made from Marine Grade Bronze, with 316 Stainless Steel available as a special order option. The top covers (collecting covers) are made from Silium, an aluminum alloy. The frame is Nodular Cast Iron. These materials are specifically selected for mineral oil and fuel separation applications.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer group-open:mb-3">Is the Alfa Laval MOPX 207 available in an explosion-proof configuration?</summary>
      <p class="text-text text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Yes, the Alfa Laval MOPX 207 is available in a Class 1 Division 2 explosion-proof configuration, making it suitable for hazardous environments where flammable fuels and solvents are processed. This explosion-proof variant, sometimes referred to as the MAPX-207, is commonly used in diesel fuel processing, biodiesel production, and other applications involving volatile hydrocarbons. Contact Dolphin Centrifuge for pricing and availability of explosion-proof MOPX 207 centrifuge systems.
      </p>
    </details>
    <details class="border-l-4 border-gold bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm p-5">
      <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer group-open:mb-3">What is the Dolphin Centrifuge equivalent of the Alfa Laval MOPX 207?</summary>
      <p class="text-text text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The <a href="/centrifuges/dmpx-028/" class="text-navy underline hover:text-gold">Dolphin DMPX-028</a> is the complete system module equivalent of the Alfa Laval MOPX 207 centrifuge bowl. The DMPX-028 adds a full system frame, PLC controls, electric heaters, feed pump, and piping to the MOPX 207 bowl to create a turnkey centrifuge module rated at 20–28 GPM on diesel depending on configuration. Contact Dolphin Centrifuge at <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold">(248) 522-2573</a> for pricing.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>

